poem she chose to walk alone though others wondered why refused to look before her kept eyes cast upwards towards the sky she didn't have companions no need for earthly things only wanted freedom from what she felt were puppet strings she longed to be a bird that she might fly away she pitied every blade of grass for planted they would stay she longed to be a flame that brightly danced alone felt jealous of the steam that made the air its only home some say she wished too hard some say she wished too long but we awoke one autumn day to find that she was gone the trees they say stood witness the sky refused to tell but someone who had seen it said the story played out well she spread her arms out wide breathed in the break of dawn she just let go of all she held and then she was gone if you wrote that you need to write more soon Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Cupid and Psyche Ayyavazhi mythology Shaggy dog story One Tree Hill (TV series) Sin City Naruto jutsu The Amber Spyglass EastEnders Characters of Naruto Avenue Q Piccolo Junior Saga The Vile Village Cosmic Era episode list Mid-Autumn Festival The Wizard of Oz (1939 film) The Star Wars Holiday Special Salad Fingers Shen Gong Wu Hyakujuu Sentai GaoRanger K' Kodocha Capercaillie Archery Conversion of Dale-Gudbrand The Wonderful Wizard of Oz Professional wrestling holds Tag Apocalyptic and post-apocalyptic science fiction Rachel Corrie Tris Speaker The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time Rave Master Neil Gaiman The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Jade Emperor Drowning Diving Jehovah's Witnesses Saruman Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Father's Day (Doctor Who) Milton H. Erickson Puppet Scarlet's Walk Sonic the Hedgehog The Death Gate Cycle Unidentified flying object Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword Equine conformation Once More, With Feeling (Buffy episode) Bernice Summerfield My Sassy Girl Knife Hide and Q (TNG episode) Light pollution Pysanka Another World (TV series) Professional wrestling throws Jabberwocky 